Heh, Japan I love ya. So, this is a girl power film written by a pervert. The girls are cute. It spoofs Power Rangers pretty dead on. The story is in no way deep. The action is fluff. It is like this was made for 6 year olds, except for showing off the lady curves. Would have been 5 stars if there were nudity, blood, tentacles, or intense recharging sessions. As it is this is a stupid, cute, sorta sexy exploitation film to spend a little while with. You could try and tell your wife/girlfriend it is a coming of age girl power film but be ready for the bruises that come with such lies ;)

Yes, the power of the breast is what powers these rangers. It's nice to know that by glancing that their boobs powers their energy to fight evil. If so sign me up. The wrestler who acts as one the rangers also sings at the end in the credits. Nice voice. All in all it great pg-13 action. No nudity.

Actually not. This is a fun Japanese sci-fi action film with a lot of beautiful Japanese women on display acting, or at least giving acting a good try, and battling their way through the bad guys! No Oscar nominations here, but a heck of a lot of great fun and eye candy!

This is hilariously bad.  I'm not sure you're supposed to take this as anything more than a "safe for work" porn film.  The plot was horrible, consisting mostly about how their power comes from guy's interest in their chest region.  The fight scenes were comically bad, and you can tell that the actresses have never thrown a decent punch in their lives.  The outfits were about on par with anime, they were revealing without being excessively trashy.

If you enjoy movies that are over the top and comically bad, then you'll enjoy this movie.  Solid 5/7

Well, if you ever wanted to know what a Japanese version of Baywatch would look like, here's your chance!

Yes, it was meant to be "goofy", "wacky", "cheesy", etc. The "regular" audiences who watch these sub-cultural movies are not expecting good storylines, acting and awesome CGI or anything. If they do, it's just a bonus point. The original Japanese title already indicates its cheesiness: "Bakunyu Sentai" Pai Ranger" (The large breasted sentai breast rangers). "pai" means "breast." LOL The props (monsters and costumes) are more than decent for this kind of movies.

Just enjoy its wackiness and girls' skin exposures.

There was barely enough story for a 15-minute television episode.  The acting was elementary school level at best.  The effects were practically non-existent.  And somewhere in this mess I find the genius of a movie without pretension.  This movie didn't trick me into thinking it was something else and it never tried.  Once you go below zero stars, there's only one thing left...  Five Stars.  An excellent find.

Surprisingly fun. Far from being serious, this could have been much worse. Most of the camera work, editing, and script were handled well. The premise pulls from sentai tropes while adding a cleavage spin. I was pleasantly surprised that the cleavage did not completely supplant the story.
